ance of outdoor recreation and sports to conservation in a collection important for fly anglers and scholars of fisheries ecology, conservation history, and environmental ethics, Backcasts explores both the problems anglers and their organizations face and how they might serve as models of conservation—in the individual trout streams, watersheds, and landscapes through which these waters flow.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aFishesxConservation. 0aFly fishing - Environmental aspects. 0aFly fishingxEnvironmental aspects. 0aFly fishing. 7aNATURE / General.2bisacsh  aFly fishing history.  acoldwater.  aconservation.  aenvironmental history.  ariver management.  asalmonids.  atrout.1 aBerryman, Jack W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBorgelt, Bryon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBorgelt, Bryon, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBrown, Jen Corrinne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrown, Jen Corrinne.1 aBruen, Matthew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDraper, Malcolm, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHoffmann, Richard C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHoriuchi, Masanori, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aImpson, Dean, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKeeling, Arn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLane, Brent, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLokensgard, Ken, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aO’Brien, Greg, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSaikku, Mik